ARRAY
array is a finite ordered collection of homogenous elements. the main adv of array is it improves code readability disadv of an array
1.the array size is fixed size
2.insertion and deletion of an element in middle of the array is difficult.
syntax:
datatype arr[]=new datatype[size]
size: char,byte,short,int.
initialization:
1.compile time:At the time of declaring an array if you are assign values to array is called compiletime initialization.
int x[]={10,20,30,40};
for(datatype ele:arrayname)
{
}
2.run time: At the time of program 
